#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=Did you follow America 's Next Top Model before appearing on the show , and if so , who did you like ?
#Text=Who did n't [ follow Top Model ] !
#Text=I was a Top Model fiend in the first couple of cycles it was on the air .
#Text=I loved Yaya because she was the educated chocolate " sista " [ who was ] much like myself .
#Text=If you could quickly summarize your experience on the show , how would you describe it ?
#Text=It was an absolutely memorable experience that I would n't change for anything in the world .
#Text=Not too many people can they say that they 've been a participant on a television series that has literally changed the face of popular culture in America and in countries worldwide .
#Text=What do your friends and family think of your stint on reality TV ?
#Text=I think everyone was really excited for me .
#Text=I think their general sentiments are that it 's cool to see someone that you know inside and out be put on display for the whole world to see .
#Text=I know there were times where I would make certain faces or have certain reactions and they would always say , " I know exactly what you were thinking . "
#Text=What were some of your specific pros and cons as a result of entering this contest ?
#Text=On the pro side , I would have to say that the exposure is incredible .
#Text=I could n't imagine how I would have been propelled into the industry so quickly if I had n't been on the show .
#Text=On the con side , I 'm not exactly sure what the show 's impression is on the fashion industry .
#Text=I try to always remain positive , though .
#Text=I , personally , have definitely used the show to my advantage as best I know how .
#Text=Impact
#Text=Top Model has on society
#Text=Do you ever fear what negative effect the show will have on girls ?
#Text=I said before that ANTM has changed the face of popular culture in America and beyond and I 'll say it again .
#Text=We 're living in a " Top Model Era . "
#Text=Every girl , woman , boy and man wants to be a model now .
#Text=But everyone cannot be a model .
#Text=Modeling is not just an " easy " way to bring in the big bucks .
#Text=It takes hard work , dedication , some hustle , and it 's not meant for everyone .
#Text=I kind of feel like ANTM is selling a false dream for a lot of folks out there .
#Text=Do you think that in some way the show can lead to girls developing an obsession with how they look , their weight , etc ?
#Text=I have to say no on this one .
#Text=I applaud the show for their consistent efforts to try to show their viewers that beauty comes in all shapes , forms , sizes , colors , and creeds .
#Text=I think that it has actually had a profoundly positive effect on the folks who watch .
#Text=I ca n't tell you how many people stop me on the street or e-mail me just to thank me for being a role model and showing the world that very thing .
